**Status:** Preprint Available (ChemRxiv) | In Revision for *Journal of Chemical Information and Modeling (JCIM)*

This project targets **Beta-secretase 1 (BACE1)**, the rate-limiting enzyme in the generation of amyloid-$\beta$ peptides. Traditional discovery pipelines have failed to balance blood-brain barrier (BBB) permeability with the selectivity required for this aspartic protease.

Addressing the exhaustion of existing chemical libraries, the IDD Lab developed a dual-pronged generative framework. We synthesized the predictive power of **Reinforcement Learning (RL)** and **Genetic Algorithms (GA)** to explore novel chemical space, validated by rigorous **Molecular Dynamics (MD)** simulations.

